title: Wilderness' Cline Wins Weekly NAHL Honor
text:
Wilderness' Cline Wins Weekly NAHL Honor 
By Zach Schneider Wilderness' Cline Wins Weekly NAHL Honor October 19, 2015 Updated Oct 19, 2015 at 5:39 PM CDT 
Cloquet, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- Minnesota Wilderness forward Tyler Cline has been named the North American Hockey League (NAHL) Midwest Division player of the week, it was announced on Monday afternoon. 
Cline scored four goals and added three assists in two Minnesota wins this past week, and his 17 total points are second-best in the NAHL this 2015-16 season. 
â€œTyler has been I big offensive boast for our team since returning to the lineup," head coach Corey Millen said. "His leadership and confidence has been very helpful for our young guys." 
Minnesota is currently on a six-game winning streak and is (8-3-1) overall.
